description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Improvement Lead NHS England and NHS Improvement South West&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for an exciting new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Improvement Lead post is a new role designed to support the Head of Improvement Capability for the South West region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are ambitious, this role is integral to ensuring we deliver our own goals and also to shape how we work with organisations across the South West Region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This opportunity comes at a unique time. We have valuable learning to take forward into how we work for the future in addition to our previous knowledge skills and expertise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be a highly experienced improvement coach and practitioner. They will demonstrate significant experience and success in designing, supporting and delivering measurable and sustainable improvement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be both demanding and highly rewarding, it will require:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to Improvement coaching and staff development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for improving quality of care and the experience patients and their families have of our services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to making improvement skills accessible and relevant to everyday activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working at a senior level to identify improvement priorities, develop improvement plans and work collaboratively to deliver improved care for patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working a senior level to coach, train and facilitate improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the experience detailed in the job description and person specification, we would be delighted to receive your application&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is based in the South West Region, based from any one of our regional offices. On lifting of current travel restrictions there will be a requirement to travel across the SW region, with occasional national travel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Ann Hill, Head of Improvement Capability (ann.hill3@nhs.net)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
